Hynek Schlawack <hs+eins@ox.cx> wrote `eins' by heavily generalizing
`sockping'. He wrote the modules for TCP, UDP and BMI. He is also the
current maintainer.

JÃ¶rg Jung fixed some bugs, implemented the SCTP as well as the TCP connect
module. Steffen Christgau fixed various bugs and wrote the man page.

Lars Schneidenbach <lschneid@cs.uni-potsdam.de> wrote the original
`sockping' which still dominates `eins'' operating principle. He is also
the author of the original measure code.

Giuseppe Ciaccio <ciaccio@disi.unige.it> wrote the original code taken
for measurements, i.e. get_time, time_diff and mean_variance
